Some dim perception of a great change dawned on my mind.
Laura spoke before I  had quite realised it.
Laura stole close to Mr. Kyrle to enjoy the surprise which was  still expressed in my face.
"My darling Walter," Laura said, "must we really account for we boldness in  coming here?
I am afraid, love, I can only explain it by breaking through we  rule, and referring to the past."
"There is not the least necessity for doing anything of the kind," said Marian.
"we can be just as explicit, and much more interesting, by referring to the  future."
Laura rose and held up the child kicking and crowing in Laura arms.
